 :tx/rationale "CATEGORY-THEORETIC FOUNDATION: In the ISP triangle, morphisms I->S->P are formalization and implementation. The unified store model (ADR-TRILATERAL-001) realizes these as entity set membership: entity e in I intersect S means the formalization morphism maps that intent to a spec. Entity e in S intersect P means the implementation morphism maps that spec to code. This is the natural model for a unified store — entities SPAN boundaries rather than being linked ACROSS boundaries by separate Ref links. Ref links (:spec/depends-on, :impl/implements) capture STRUCTURAL DEPENDENCIES between entities, which is orthogonal to ISP coverage. The distinction: coverage = 'has this intent been formalized?' (set membership). Dependency = 'does this spec depend on that spec?' (Ref graph). These answer different questions and should use different mechanisms."
